<i>Posted by Crydee Ossiriand on 10-26-2001 04:59 AM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/Shy_Face.gif" alt="" width="15" height="15" border="0"> Epic Scam - read if you dont have epics yet</b></p>

<p>If this was in the least bit trivial, I'd pass it to one of my friends to post for me. Some things you just have to do yourself just to make sure they get down. This is one of them...<br />
<br />
I'm miding my own business, when I get a doozy of an email from a ranger on Quellious who got cheated out of Earthcaller by a scammer. BTW - If you are on this guys server and can help out with recovering from the loss, it would be appreciated. =)<br />
<br />
<br />
Keep in mind that I generally do not reprint emails that are sent to me.<br />
<blockquote><FONT face="arial,helvetica" size="1">quote:</font><hr>-----Original Message-----<br />
From:  <br />
Sent: Thursday, October 25, 2001 2:32 PM<br />
To: <a href="mailto:crydee@questing-ranger.com">crydee@questing-ranger.com</a><br />
Subject: Epic scam, please pass this on<br />
<br />
<br />
Hello,<br />
<br />
I am sending this to you in hopes that future occurrences of this won't happen.  My character is Vytor Vexxen, 56th Ranger on the Quellious server.  Last Sunday 10/22/01, I was scammed out of the final piece of my epic.  I have had Swiftwind for about 4 months now and have been on countless PoH raids trying to get my last piece.  I have had no luck whatsoever.  On Sunday I was in EC and don't ask me why (sheer stupidity) I auctioned to trade for the MQ'ing of the Shattered Emerald of Corruption.  About a minute later a 14th lv Bard gave me a tell, his name was Xeba.  Xeba told me he had one on his rogue that had been in the bank forever.  We chatted for a minute and I told him to log to his Rogue.  I wanted to get his name and toss it around in guildchat to see if anyone knew who he was.  The Rogue's name was Backs.  Backs was a lv 53 Rogue and I thought to myself, well, I have been playing for nearly 2 years and am lv 56, so I found it believable that he could have the Emerald.  I spoke to my guildmates and the general consensus was Backs was a pretty reputable guy, and they thought he was trustworthy.  Unfortunately this wasn't the case.  We went to NK to hand the final piece in.  I made him hail the tree and did everything correctly (all the faction stuff was fine).  He told me he handed in his piece, and said it was fine if I handed mine in.  So I did.  To my dismay I got absolutely nothing in return.  No Earthcaller, no nothing.  It made me sick to my stomach.  I couldn't believe the months of work I had done were gone.  I have petitioned and spoken to the server GM, but there will be no reimbursement.  Basically I was told since it was a MQ, there is nothing he could do.  He did however lead me to believe the person I was dealing may not have been completely honest with me.  Now mind you, I only gave this guy a Blood Point, and was supposed to give him additional items later on.  The GM also told me to ask around and talk to other Rangers.  He also led me to believe there was a way to quest just one of the swords!?!  If you have any knowledge of this PLEASE reply to my e-mail.  Anyhow, later that night I did some homework and found out that at least 2 other Rangers had been scammed by this guy, in exactly the same manner.  The next time you post information could you please post something to this effect and let people know about this person that continues to scam people out of all their hard work.  I know how I felt after this happened and would hate to see it happen to someone else.  Thanks for your time.<br />
<br />
Thanks,<br />
Vytor Vexxen<br />
Ranger of the 56th Season<hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
<br />
I'm going back on vacation now.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
