<i>Posted by Duncynn on 10-26-2001 05:21 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>I think this shows a couple of things.  First of all we are trying to play a game that is as close to virtual reality as we get in 2001.  Second this game (as all roleplaying games) are steeped in good vs evil.  This was evil and if this guy was roleplaying an evil character, it could have well been in his "code" to do this.  Now I don't think this is true, I think he is a punk, but it makes you think.  Reward is valueless unless it comes with risk.  I don't know how many Hate raids I went on before my stone dropped but I would never have trusted anyone but a close friend to MQ this, in the same way I wouldn't ask a total stranger to transfer 10k (or even 100pp) between characters.<br />
<br />
There is a reason that Verant does not support MQ'ing and we should not skip casually through Norath thinking that everyone is good and just.  There are bad people out there in fantasy land  as there is in real life.  We should protect ourselves against them.  I don't think Verant has a responsibility (nor should they) to protect ourselves from poor judgement.  I think there is a lesson to be learned for all of us.<br />
<br />
Having said all this, I am sorry a fellow Ranger got scammed and if I were on his serrver, I would attempt to help him back to where he needs to be.  Maybe the Rangers of that server can band together to do this.  Because, for every scum like this guy, there are many good and honorable real people behind those charatcers on the screen.  And many of them play Rangers!<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
